      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im studying structural mechanics and im a bit stuck on cantilevers. specifically for a balcony design. can u explain how a cantilevered beam actually stays stable since there is no vertical support at the outer edge? i know it involves moment and torque but i dont really get how the fixed end manages the rotation stress.",
